                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/403.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Having received various inquiries from American citizens regarding payment of
                    mining taxes in Mexico I obtained the following instructions from Sr. Ignacio
                    Bonillas, Acting Secretary: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>For payment of mining tax address Director General del Timbre, Mexico
                            City, giving name of mine, number of pertenencias, location of mine in
                            municipality, district, partido or canton, and state, name of party to
                            whom title was issued, name of present owner, time for which the tax is
                            due with the understanding that no payment made to officer of the Huerta
                            Government since March 1st, 1913, is valid; if the last boleta is sent
                            it will facilitate matters; if not give number of the title as well as
                            the number of registry of the same. The tax is six pesos per pertenencia
                            or fraction thereof per year payable every third of a year.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
